">This translates that the patented invention contributes positively to the advancement of technology and improves the lives of those who utilize it.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Non-Obvious\"><\/span><b>Non-Obvious<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As per the laws and rights governing intellectual property, it is essential that an app idea be non-obvious to an experienced person in the same field.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This stipulation ensures that the individual evaluating the patent application has the authority to accurately categorize it.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It not only promotes innovation by encouraging unique ideas but also prevents the patenting of minor modifications to existing technologies.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"How_to_Check_If_a_Similar_App_Idea_Is_Patented_or_Not\"><\/span>How to Check If a Similar App Idea Is Patented or Not?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For your surprise, there is a complete database that holds all the information about the m<\/span>obile app ideas<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> filed for patenting.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With this invaluable resource, app owners can sift through existing patents and identify potential gaps in the market.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This database guarantees app ideas are unique and do not infringe upon any intellectual property rights.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Through the World Intellectual Property Organization&#8217;s International Patent Classification (IPC) Catchword Index, it is possible to explore existing mobile app ideas that have already been filed for an international patent.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At the same time, if the pate